			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">If you get the chance next time Xal ask him about defensive spells or abilities for magicians?
<br />

<br />
We all know a necro has the most, a wizard has rune skins and insta evac, a real get out of jail free card, and enchanters are with necro's in a mirad of ways to get out of troubel free cards. There is no use saying that a pet is the only answer because if it were, than why isn't that the same for a necro? The pet for a mage when it hits the fan is to buy us time to run or gate, well a necro pet does the same exact function and as they have an invunerability shield that is fast casting, their pet only needs hold off the mobs long enough to cast it and run, or FD (holding the invunerability shield in reserve), and of course with a rune shield they can take a few hits for no damage etc...
<br />

<br />
Why am I going into this all again, we all know the defense of a pet IS not enough, when a necro has the SAME EXACT defense, when our pet die and a necro pet dies, we both can run or gate. The difference is a necro has a slew more options including rooting the mob to make their escape. The notion that our pets are a lot better doesn't hold water any longer, becasue the issue is when the pet is dead for both classes, the mage asks for a res, the necro has a slew of options, and if they all fail he can res themselves. This is NOT BALLANCE and I am tired of this bull shit notion that our pets is all we need for a defense, we need something for when the pet dies like every other class in the game has but us.
<br />

<br />
Calebe<br />_________________<br />Level 65 Magician
<br />
E'CI Server
<br />
Infinit</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
